the mortar and pestle for this…]

1236
00:47:27,650 --> 00:47:28,740
Just give it a mix.

1237
00:47:28,290 --> 00:47:32,590
[Mix it casually and you're done]

1238
00:47:32,760 --> 00:47:35,960
[The rice is good to go…
Should I make some soup?]

1239
00:47:36,460 --> 00:47:38,460
I'll make bean paste stew.

1240
00:47:37,130 --> 00:47:41,410
[Cucumber gimbap with bean paste stew]

1241
00:47:42,120 --> 00:47:44,520
[Feat. Shepherd's purse]

1242
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:47,160
I washed the clams thoroughly
and removed the sand. Good to go.

1243
00:47:45,090 --> 00:47:47,350
[(Plus the clams)]

1244
00:47:47,740 --> 00:47:51,360
[Hong Jinkyung: Adding the clams
will make the taste richer and stronger.]

1245
00:47:51,670 --> 00:47:52,900
It will taste better.

1246
00:47:54,390 --> 00:47:57,780
[Should I remove the shells?
It's easier to eat that way, right?]

1247
00:47:57,830 --> 00:47:59,740
[Focused]

1248
00:48:00,320 --> 00:48:01,680
It's easier to eat that way.

1249
00:48:00,660 --> 00:48:06,170
[Clams are hand-shucked one by one]

1250
00:48:04,350 --> 00:48:05,040
Done.

1251
00:48:07,300 --> 00:48:09,790
[Now, just ladle it out and we're done!]

1252
00:48:10,680 --> 00:48:15,120
[Wrap up the lunchbox with a cloth]

1253
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:14,960
Wrap these up.

1254
00:48:16,280 --> 00:48:18,460
[Need to pack the ice cream too!]

1255
00:48:18,830 --> 00:48:23,090
I'll make the ice cream first
and freeze it in the freezer.

1256
00:48:19,010 --> 00:48:23,190
[Last night]

1257
00:48:23,790 --> 00:48:27,490
[In the vanilla ice cream]

1258
00:48:24,420 --> 00:48:27,510
Our whole family used to
eat this together, digging in with spoons.

1259
00:48:27,510 --> 00:48:28,880
Now let's add

1260
00:48:29,940 --> 00:48:31,970
just one spoon. Like this.

1261
00:48:29,960 --> 00:48:32,990
[Hits Hae-in's sweet spot—
add a scoop of whiskey!]

1262
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:35,800
[Uh-huh~]

1263
00:48:33,920 --> 00:48:35,780
The whiskey aroma is so strong.

1264
00:48:35,860 --> 00:48:38,900
[An unexpected perfect match]

1265
00:48:35,990 --> 00:48:39,010
But it feels great when it's mixed
with the scent of ice cream.

1266
00:48:39,010 --> 00:48:41,320
Getting tipsy from eating ice cream.

1267
00:48:39,570 --> 00:48:42,930
[The whiskey ice cream
with a (tiny?) buzz is done]

1268
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:43,650
And you don't even need
any drinking snacks.

1269
00:48:43,650 --> 00:48:45,610
[Jinkyung finishes up
the rest of the ice cream]

1270
00:48:46,580 --> 00:48:48,770
[The ice cream is for dessert!]

1271
00:48:49,570 --> 00:48:55,300
[Packs the main dish and dessert neatly]

1272
00:48:55,530 --> 00:49:00,450
[Home-cooked Lunch Box,
Handmade by: Hong Jinkyung]

1273
00:49:00,450 --> 00:49:04,070
[Jung Hae-in, Gangnam District]

1274
00:49:01,960 --> 00:49:03,140
He's here.

1275
00:49:04,570 --> 00:49:05,920
[I know where he is!]

1276
00:49:07,430 --> 00:49:11,700
[Set out to see Hae-in
with all the gifts]

1277
00:49:11,700 --> 00:49:15,540
[Hong Jinkyung, Jung Hae-in]

1278
00:49:16,520 --> 00:49:20,190
[On the other side,
Namno is taking a breather]

1279
00:49:19,220 --> 00:49:20,040
Okay.

1280
00:49:20,780 --> 00:49:23,730
[It should've been done five minutes ago]

1281
00:49:20,900 --> 00:49:23,630
Then I need to have it ready
five minutes early.

1282
00:49:23,630 --> 00:49:25,100
Five minutes? Can we make it?

1283
00:49:23,940 --> 00:49:26,320
[The second dessert]

1284
00:49:25,530 --> 00:49:26,390
I have to hurry.

1285
00:49:27,030 --> 00:49:27,540
[Last night]

1286
00:49:27,540 --> 00:49:30,980
[Last night] [Yoon Namno: I want to make
a dessert you can't get at chain stores.]

1287
00:49:31,100 --> 00:49:32,090
Mille-feuille, that's it.

1288
00:49:31,240 --> 00:49:32,950
[Mille-feuille]

1289
00:49:33,260 --> 00:49:37,430
[Mille-feuille: A classic French pastry
layered with custard or chocolate cream]

1290
00:49:33,640 --> 00:49:36,300
There are two kinds of cream
in a mille-feuille.

1291
00:49:37,670 --> 00:49:39,180
One is vanilla cream.

1292
00:49:37,780 --> 00:49:40,930
[Vanilla and chocolate] [Mille-feuille
filled with two kinds of cream]

1293
00:49:39,180 --> 00:49:40,910
The other is chocolate cream.

1294
00:49:41,390 --> 00:49:44,890
[Makes the mille-feuille
with all his heart]

1295
00:49:47,530 --> 00:49:50,560
[Vanilla bean custard]

1296
00:49:49,330 --> 00:49:51,010
Put it into the mille-feuille.

1297
00:49:51,010 --> 00:49:52,970
Wow, it's tiring, but it's fun.

1298
00:49:51,180 --> 00:49:54,640
[Yoon Namno: Wow!
It's tiring, but it's fun.]

1299
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:58,990
[Sweet and rich chocolate cream]

1300
00:49:59,410 --> 00:50:01,610
Why are my legs feeling a little wobbly?

1301
00:50:01,970 --> 00:50:04,050
[Starts stacking]

1302
00:50:04,280 --> 00:50:08,190
[Meticulous]

1303
00:50:08,540 --> 00:50:11,970
[The one being made
is a sample mille-feuille]

1304
00:50:12,450 --> 00:50:14,960
[The real gift]
[He's going to make it on site tomorrow]

1305
00:50:13,220 --> 00:50:15,020
Lastly, put some strawberries.

1306
00:50:15,490 --> 00:50:18,850
[Manito symbol]

1307
00:50:15,700 --> 00:50:18,840
This is our symbol.

1308
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:21,680
Stamp the chocolate with it.

1309
00:50:19,370 --> 00:50:22,690
[Making chocolate with the Manito symbol]

1310
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:37,420
[The second gift: Mille-feuille]

1311
00:50:32,060 --> 00:50:33,900
He'll like them, right?

1312
00:50:38,140 --> 00:50:41,050
[Okay, let's go!]

1313
00:50:42,020 --> 00:50:44,160
[Proudly going to work the second time]

1314
00:50:45,240 --> 00:50:49,090
[His stride became more imposing]

1315
00:50:49,810 --> 00:50:52,800
[Chose the stairs
rather than the elevator]

1316
00:50:53,600 --> 00:50:56,470
[Meanwhile, Hae-in
is back to the shooting]

1317
00:50:57,310 --> 00:50:59,340
[Settles down by the stairs next door]

1318
00:51:00,780 --> 00:51:04,090
[Builds a simple kitchen
in the corner immediately]

1319
00:51:04,700 --> 00:51:10,070
[Before the shooting finishes,
he has to be ready]

1320
00:51:07,940 --> 00:51:10,740
Come on, hurry up.

1321
00:51:10,550 --> 00:51:13,440
[Starts making with the ingredients
prepared yesterday]

1322
00:51:14,310 --> 00:51:15,810
[Uh oh, hands are shaking]

1323
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:18,410
[Shaking]

1324
00:51:19,450 --> 00:51:23,800
[Making the mille-feuille
with shaking hands]

1325
00:51:21,680 --> 00:51:23,060
I can do it. I can do it.

1326
00:51:23,060 --> 00:51:24,110
It's almost done.

1327
00:51:24,120 --> 00:51:27,210
[Getting it done is more important
than making it look pretty]

1328
00:51:27,580 --> 00:51:29,630
[Ah! Oh my. (Shaking)]

1329
00:51:29,730 --> 00:51:30,610
Don't fall down, please.

1330
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:32,230
[Keeps shaking]

1331
00:51:33,230 --> 00:51:33,730
[(Slips away)]

1332
00:51:33,730 --> 00:51:35,330
[Ah]

1333
00:51:35,930 --> 00:51:38,030
[Chocolate! Uh-huh.
Need to put the chocolate on it too.]

1334
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:40,920
[And didn't forget
the handmade Manito chocolate]

1335
00:51:39,690 --> 00:51:40,890
I'll just put it here.

1336
00:51:41,810 --> 00:51:43,450
[Need to put more gold dust]

1337
00:51:44,930 --> 00:51:47,130
[There's even gold dust
for the finishing touch]

1338
00:51:48,390 --> 00:51:51,210
[Uh oh, don't open it. Don't open it.
Don't open it.]

1339
00:51:51,220 --> 00:51:52,680
[Don't do anything!]

1340
00:51:51,980 --> 00:51:52,410
Now…

1341
00:51:53,200 --> 00:51:56,560
[Why are the lights off?
Because of nerves, everything is on hold]

1342
00:51:57,300 --> 00:52:00,960
[Finally, the mille-feuille is done]

1343
00:52:05,900 --> 00:52:08,910
[Wet] [My legs are shaking…]

1344
00:52:09,580 --> 00:52:13,960
[In an instant, the shooting
is close to the end too]

1345
00:52:18,540 --> 00:52:20,500
[Unlike when he was making the dessert,
he's running over without hesitation]

1346
00:52:21,120 --> 00:52:23,010
[Opens the door]

1347
00:52:24,180 --> 00:52:31,850
[Hae-in is in the middle of shooting]
[Sneaks in from the back boldly]

1348
00:52:32,460 --> 00:52:34,500
[Striding]

1349
00:52:35,520 --> 00:52:38,610
[Sending the gifts calmly]

1350
00:52:39,900 --> 00:52:43,500
[The letter of dual personality
is also placed alongside]

1351
00:52:44,980 --> 00:52:47,320
[The applause signals the break time]

1352
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:52,280
[Leaves calmly after sending the gift]

1353
00:52:55,180 --> 00:52:58,270
[Getting closer and closer]

1354
00:52:58,600 --> 00:53:02,140
[Jung Hae-in] [In a rush, almost forgot
to post the letter to the staff]

1355
00:53:07,020 --> 00:53:09,690
[Exits calmly]

1356
00:53:09,950 --> 00:53:12,370
[Jung Hae-in]

1357
00:53:14,030 --> 00:53:15,460
[Sprints away]

1358
00:53:16,130 --> 00:53:19,060
[A familiar escape scene]

1359
00:53:19,440 --> 00:53:21,440
[Done! Done!]

1360
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:23,630
[Ahhhhh!]

1361
00:53:25,900 --> 00:53:28,220
[Ahhh! Hahahaha!]

1362
00:53:30,450 --> 00:53:31,410
[Exhales…]

1363
00:53:31,440 --> 00:53:32,260
[Exhales…]

1364
00:53:32,400 --> 00:53:33,470
[Uh… My heart is beating so fast…]

1365
00:53:33,880 --> 00:53:36,590
[Because of running too fast, this is
a natural reaction of the human body]

1366
00:53:37,760 --> 00:53:40,800
[I'm going to throw up.]

1367
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:40,970
Done.

1368
00:53:41,450 --> 00:53:43,660
[Ah~ Lunchbox!
I have to go make the lunchbox…]

1369
00:53:43,660 --> 00:53:46,070
[Namno's day is not over yet]

1370
00:53:49,170 --> 00:53:51,030
[Uh, what's this!]

1371
00:53:51,780 --> 00:53:53,600
[Hae-in?]

1372
00:53:55,110 --> 00:53:57,900
[I made this mille-feuille myself.
Hope you enjoy it.]

1373
00:53:58,450 --> 00:54:03,260
[It's a dessert as sweet as you!
From: Oppa's Manito]

1374
00:54:03,520 --> 00:54:05,850
[The plate needs to be recycled. Hahaha]

1375
00:54:06,240 --> 00:54:09,150
[After reading this one letter,
he's more curious about the next one]

1376
00:54:09,610 --> 00:54:12,430
[Jung Hae-in, do you usually eat on time?]

1377
00:54:12,760 --> 00:54:16,790
[Please share with the staff!
P.S.: Your Manito Bro]

1378
00:54:17,090 --> 00:54:20,240
[Wait a second… I have two Manitos?]

1379
00:54:20,590 --> 00:54:22,240
[A perfect dual personality]

1380
00:54:23,260 --> 00:54:25,030
[Wow, but the mille-feuille is amazing~]

1381
00:54:25,620 --> 00:54:27,050
[Jung Hae-in: How can you
make this yourself…]

1382
00:54:27,050 --> 00:54:28,770
[Jung Hae-in: There's even
gold dust on it!]

1383
00:54:30,540 --> 00:54:32,840
[The appearance makes you go "wow"]

1384
00:54:32,240 --> 00:54:33,040
This is crazy.

1385
00:54:33,860 --> 00:54:37,060
[Takes a bite immediately]

1386
00:54:37,560 --> 00:54:40,230
[His face says it all about the taste]

1387
00:54:40,650 --> 00:54:43,880
[Takes a big bite immediately]

1388
00:54:45,280 --> 00:54:47,780
[Jung Hae-in: Wow.
But if it's at this level]

1389
00:54:45,560 --> 00:54:46,960
But if it's at this level,

1390
00:54:48,110 --> 00:54:52,550
[Jung Hae-in: he's really
a talented pastry chef.]

1391
00:54:53,170 --> 00:54:56,440
[Jung Hae-in: The chocolate here
even has the Manito symbol on it!]

1392
00:54:56,740 --> 00:54:58,870
[Touched by the thoughtful details]

1393
00:54:56,950 --> 00:54:58,120
Thank you so much.

1394
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:01,740
[Jung Hae-in: The plate actually
looks quite expensive.]

1395
00:55:01,740 --> 00:55:03,170
[Jung Hae-in: I'll make sure
to return it properly~]

1396
00:55:03,170 --> 00:55:05,940
[But I need to know who it is
in order to return it. Hahaha.]

1397
00:55:05,940 --> 00:55:07,760
[After reading the letter] [Jung Hae-in:
The staff must have got some too, right?]

1398
00:55:11,730 --> 00:55:14,060
[Found it nearby right away]

1399
00:55:14,800 --> 00:55:16,460
[Wow~]

1400
00:55:17,350 --> 00:55:19,080
[Please take care of Hae-in! Please enjoy!
These snacks are for the staff!]

1401
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:20,810
[A warm heart that also
reaches those around him]

1402
00:55:21,370 --> 00:55:23,080
[Jung Hae-in: Awesome…]

1403
00:55:24,470 --> 00:55:26,370
[So many financiers]
[Wow… When was this made?]

1404
00:55:26,370 --> 00:55:28,140
[My Manito is…]

1405
00:55:28,320 --> 00:55:30,780
[A cafe owner?]

1406
00:55:31,790 --> 00:55:34,010
[Oh, so cold]

1407
00:55:34,550 --> 00:55:38,000
[Meanwhile, a person who doesn't look like
a cafe owner is approaching]

1408
00:55:39,760 --> 00:55:41,910
[Sighs… So excited]

1409
00:55:40,630 --> 00:55:41,580
I'm so excited.

1410
00:55:43,380 --> 00:55:44,490
I generally don't eat while shooting.

1411
00:55:43,500 --> 00:55:47,620
[He's still praising the mille-feuille]

1412
00:55:44,540 --> 00:55:47,400
But this is really delicious.
Try it. It's amazing.

1413
00:55:47,880 --> 00:55:49,450
[(Name Not Revealed):
Your delivery has arrived.] [Oh, what?]

1414
00:55:49,600 --> 00:55:51,470
[Oh, you scared me.]

1415
00:55:52,090 --> 00:55:54,390
[I'm here to deliver food.]

1416
00:55:54,780 --> 00:55:56,060
How have you been?

1417
00:55:54,890 --> 00:55:58,460
[Here comes a Manito senior]

1418
00:55:56,510 --> 00:55:57,140
Goodness!

1419
00:55:57,910 --> 00:55:58,620
Thank you!

1420
00:55:58,460 --> 00:56:00,520
[Dex: Thank you for having me, Hae-in.]

1421
00:56:00,520 --> 00:56:02,860
[Jung Hae-in: My reliable backup is here.]

1422
00:56:02,860 --> 00:56:04,920
[Dex: How do I look, Hae-in?]

1423
00:56:06,120 --> 00:56:07,110
You look quite like it.

1424
00:56:06,480 --> 00:56:09,540
[Cargo pants, vest, and helmet]

1425
00:56:07,210 --> 00:56:09,220
Perfect. If you wear the helmet,

1426
00:56:09,380 --> 00:56:10,670
you won't be recognized at all.

1427
00:56:09,880 --> 00:56:12,000
[The perfect look of a delivery man]
[This is mine.]

1428
00:56:10,740 --> 00:56:11,540
Is this yours?

1429
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:13,210
[This is mine.]

1430
00:56:12,460 --> 00:56:13,450
I brought mine.

1431
00:56:14,320 --> 00:56:16,530
[Dex: I also brought this,
a balaclava hat.]

1432
00:56:17,020 --> 00:56:17,840
[Perfect]

1433
00:56:17,840 --> 00:56:19,850
[Dex: Wearing the balaclava hat
and the helmet?]

1434
00:56:20,150 --> 00:56:22,060
[Dex: You wouldn't know who it was
even if I took off the helmet.]

1435
00:56:22,060 --> 00:56:23,620
[Dex: Because you can only see the eyes.]

1436
00:56:23,850 --> 00:56:25,840
[Jung Hae-in: But your eyes
are way too distinctive.]

1437
00:56:25,840 --> 00:56:27,700
[Jung Hae-in: I can tell right away
who you are.]

1438
00:56:27,020 --> 00:56:27,990
I'll wear my helmet to cover them then.

1439
00:56:27,990 --> 00:56:29,520
-Sit down first.
-I did this on purpose.

1440
00:56:28,050 --> 00:56:30,710
[Sit down first
and make a strategy briefing]

1441
00:56:30,710 --> 00:56:33,570
[What's this?]
[Jung Hae-in: No, I have an order…]

1442
00:56:32,540 --> 00:56:33,320
What's this?

1443
00:56:33,570 --> 00:56:36,960
[Jung Hae-in: I was doing the shooting.
My Manito sent it here and left.]

1444
00:56:36,180 --> 00:56:36,720
This?

1445
00:56:36,780 --> 00:56:38,460
This and the mille-feuille
were made by him.

1446
00:56:37,340 --> 00:56:40,800
[Can't wait to show off
the gift from his Manito]

1447
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:39,200
What?

1448
00:56:39,700 --> 00:56:40,560
And the letter.

1449
00:56:40,800 --> 00:56:41,930
[To Jung Hae-in: Do you eat on time?
Thanks for your work in shooting the ad.]

1450
00:56:41,930 --> 00:56:42,350
[You should take care of those
around you at times like this.]

1451
00:56:42,350 --> 00:56:43,060
[Share it with the staff! P.S. Your Manito
Bro] [Dex: Wait, it says "Manito Bro."]

1452
00:56:43,060 --> 00:56:45,910
[P.S.: Your Manito Bro] [Dex: But
it looks like a woman's handwriting.]

1453
00:56:45,540 --> 00:56:46,170
I know, right?

1454
00:56:46,070 --> 00:56:48,220
[Jung Hae-in: And it says "Oppa" here.]

1455
00:56:48,220 --> 00:56:49,720
[Dex: Oh, really?]

1456
00:56:49,720 --> 00:56:53,890
[From: Oppa's Manito]
[Jung Hae-in: So this is a smokescreen.]

1457
00:56:49,970 --> 00:56:51,670
So this is a smokescreen.

1458
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:52,480
Smokescreen.

1459
00:56:52,480 --> 00:56:53,280
Smokescreen.

1460
00:56:54,560 --> 00:56:56,370
[Dex: Then who's your Manito?]

1461
00:56:57,050 --> 00:57:00,620
[Ears perked up]
[Jung Hae-in: My Manito is…]

1462
00:57:01,320 --> 00:57:05,180
[Actress Go Younjung]

1463
00:57:05,350 --> 00:57:07,880
[Dex: I want to meet her in person too…]
[Chuckling]

1464
00:57:07,610 --> 00:57:08,350
Then, today, let's just…

1465
00:57:08,140 --> 00:57:09,950
[Thank you]

1466
00:57:10,140 --> 00:57:11,740
Thank you.

1467
00:57:10,270 --> 00:57:13,790
[The delivery is already worth it]

1468
00:57:11,810 --> 00:57:13,140
A dramatic compromise.

1469
00:57:13,790 --> 00:57:17,180
[Jung Hae-in: But I know
she's very generous and straightforward.]

1470
00:57:18,140 --> 00:57:20,220
[Dex: She's known for
being generous and straightforward.]

1471
00:57:20,220 --> 00:57:22,610
[Dex: And she's quite easygoing.]

1472
00:57:22,610 --> 00:57:25,220
[Jung Hae-in: She's more impulsive
than I thought.]

1473
00:57:24,740 --> 00:57:25,390
Really?

1474
00:57:25,220 --> 00:57:27,380
[Jung Hae-in: I was wearing
a helmet like you.]

1475
00:57:27,380 --> 00:57:29,200
[Jung Hae-in: I said it was
a flash delivery and gave it to her.]

1476
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:31,880
[So did she catch you?]
[Jung Hae-in: Then she ran towards me.]

1477
00:57:31,880 --> 00:57:34,530
[Jung Hae-in: She didn't catch me.
I ran away when I saw her.]

1478
00:57:33,270 --> 00:57:34,810
-You ran?
-I ran away when I saw her.

1479
00:57:34,530 --> 00:57:37,190
[Wait, what if my helmet gets pulled off?]

1480
00:57:38,790 --> 00:57:39,500
OK.

1481
00:57:39,210 --> 00:57:41,860
[Dex: What's the gift
that I need to deliver?]

1482
00:57:41,860 --> 00:57:45,520
[Ah, there's a mission?]
[Jung Hae-in: You have a mission.]

1483
00:57:45,710 --> 00:57:49,080
[Younjung likes peaches]

1484
00:57:45,830 --> 00:57:48,150
Actress Go likes peaches.

1485
00:57:48,160 --> 00:57:48,690
Peaches?

1486
00:57:48,730 --> 00:57:51,350
So there's a cafe
famous for peaches in Seongsu-dong.

1487
00:57:49,410 --> 00:57:52,460
[Knows Younjung well
and searched for the cafe]

1488
00:57:51,850 --> 00:57:52,680
I found it.

1489
00:57:52,930 --> 00:57:54,760
-You go buy the peach parfait.
-Parfait.

1490
00:57:53,410 --> 00:58:00,860
[Shopping List: ① Peach Parfait;
② Coffee; ③ Peach Shaved Ice]

1491
00:57:54,840 --> 00:57:56,330
She also likes drinking coffee.

1492
00:57:56,330 --> 00:57:57,420
Coffee.

1493
00:57:57,520 --> 00:57:59,060
And you need to buy peach shaved ice.

1494
00:57:59,060 --> 00:58:00,360
Shaved ice. Coffee.

1495
00:58:00,860 --> 00:58:03,820
[Jung Hae-in: Say "Your Manito asked me
to give this to you." Then hand it over.]

1496
00:58:04,070 --> 00:58:06,400
[Should I say "Your Manito asked me
to give it to you"?]

1497
00:58:06,400 --> 00:58:09,500
[That way, even if my identity
is uncovered, it won't cause confusion…]

1498
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:08,510
Even if my identity
is uncovered…

1499
00:58:08,530 --> 00:58:09,710
-No.
-It won't cause confusion.

1500
00:58:09,680 --> 00:58:13,570
[Aha~ Manito would hide his identity]

1501
00:58:13,050 --> 00:58:15,420
Manitos can pretend they are not Manitos.

1502
00:58:15,160 --> 00:58:18,790
[Dex: You've become a professional
after only one day.]

1503
00:58:18,790 --> 00:58:20,410
[Jung Hae-in: I need you
to deliver my letter.]

1504
00:58:20,610 --> 00:58:22,770
[Also gives him the letter
written in advance]

1505
00:58:20,710 --> 00:58:22,130
-This is the letter I wrote.
-I'll make sure…

1506
00:58:22,130 --> 00:58:23,070
I'll make sure to deliver them properly.

1507
00:58:22,780 --> 00:58:25,300
[It's okay. You can read it. It's fine.]
[Dex: I won't read the letter.]

1508
00:58:25,300 --> 00:58:26,740
[It's okay. You can read it. It's fine.]
[I'm so curious?]

1509
00:58:26,790 --> 00:58:28,440
[Hello. I'm your Manito~]

1510
00:58:28,520 --> 00:58:30,980
[I knew you ran
but I didn't expect you ran this fast.]

1511
00:58:31,260 --> 00:58:33,780
[Dex: There's still a surprise coming.
